  "text": "[12] At the upper level, the westward flowing EIC, centered on the equator, the SICC and NICC centered 2°S and 2°N respectively, both flowing eastward and the two westward mean currents centered 4°S and 4°N, called South and North Equatorial Intermediate Currents (SEIC and NEIC [CITATION_1] ]) are strong features of the intermediate equatorial circulation with peak mean velocities exceeding 10 cm s",
